the weight of her satchel on her shoulder
again she closed her eyes letting the sounds and textures swirl around her senses until she could scarcely distinguish them from her own reality
such was the power of fine writingit created an illusion so vivid so grounded that the line between reader and narrator blurred
by the time she finished the second story darkness had fallen completely
the study lamp cast a soft pool of light around her chair
beyond the window the garden was now a shadowy realm defined only by silhouettes and the glimmer of a single landing moth
inside
alice felt both exhausted and invigorated as though shed traveled far beyond the confines of her cozy study the distance a lone streetlamp flickered to life its orange glow rebounded off dewy leaves turning them into luminous orbs Alice closed the anthology pressed a finger against the spine and slid the book into its place on the shelf She sat for a moment longer teacup in hand simply being It was a practice in mindfulness in appreciating transition The end of daylight and arrival of evening the movement from narrative to reflection She allowed herself this small pause before rising to begin the next phase of her evening routine preparing a light supper writing a few thoughtful entries in her journal and perhaps stepping out onto the back porch to breathe beneath a sky of stars When she finally stood the teacup empty 